	(text "MakeLife Design Block: Reverse Polarity Protection"
		(at 76.2 25.4 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2.54 2.54)
			)
		)
		(uuid "2ba2d981-5367-41dd-8d8e-4f17c726ed0a")
	)
	(text "P-MOSFET reverse polarity protection + TVS diode.\nP-MOSFET (e.g. SI2301, IRF9540) in high-side with gate to GND via 10k.\nBody diode conducts briefly on correct polarity, then MOSFET enhances (Rds_on < 100mOhm).\nReverse polarity: gate-source = 0V, MOSFET OFF, body diode blocks.\nTVS diode (bidirectional, e.g. SMBJ30CA) across VIN-GND for surge protection.\nVoltage drop: ~50mV at 1A (vs 400mV for Schottky diode approach).\nMax voltage: depends on MOSFET Vds rating (choose >= 2x operating voltage).\nAdd 100nF ceramic cap after MOSFET for high-frequency decoupling."
		(at 76.2 38.1 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.524 1.524)
			)
		)
		(uuid "14a3675e-9768-4112-ae7b-cc3b2890ba41")
	)
